comment: Dieng (MIN) is in the lane for more than 3 seconds.
Dieng's (MIN) contact does not affect Clarkson's (LAL) RSBQ.
Clarkson (LAL) makes contact with LaVine's (MIN) body and the contact affects his ability to shoot.
Black (LAL) does not dislodge Kilpatrick (MIN).
Dieng (MIN) is not vertical on the play to the basket by Clarkson (LAL).
LHH shows Brown (MIN) makes contact with Ellington's (LAL) hand while it is in contact with the ball.
Ellington (LAL) makes contact with Wiggins' (MIN) body on the jump shot.
Concurrent fouls occur. Payne (MIN) makes contact with Black's (LAL) arm and Wiggins (MIN) makes contact to back.
LaVine (MIN) splits his feet on the perimeter.
Ellington (LAL) makes contact with Wiggins' (MIN) arm and the contact affects his play to the basket.
LaVine (MIN) knocks the ball out of Clarkson's (LAL) hands before he picks up his pivot.
The contact by Ellington (LAL) dislodges Wiggins (MIN).
Wiggins (MIN) switches his pivot foot after catching the ball.
24 Second Violation correctly called.
Brown (LAL) makes contact with Clarkson's (LAL) arm and the contact affects his play to the basket.
Black (LAL) intentionally kicks the ball on the play.
Wiggins (MIN) moves his pivot foot.
Ellington (LAL) faces up with Budinger (MIN) with his hands to his chest.

After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor that Budinger (MIN) stepped OOB was overturned. Possible foul contact preceding an OOBs play is not a reviewable matter and cannot be considered by referees when conducting reviews.
LaVine (MIN) dislodges Clarkson (MIN).
After inbound, but prior to the touch, Clarkson (LAL) grabs Wiggins' (MIN) arm, preventing him from catching the pass.
